{"lemma":"كَلْبِ","slug":"كَلْبِ","root":"ك.ل.ب","root_slug":"ك-ل-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ل-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كَلْب","root":"كلب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37137","n37138","n37142","n37143","n37144"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dog"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be seized by hydrophobia, to become rabid"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become mad, to become crazy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to covet greedily"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَلِبَ (kaliba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rabies, hydrophobia","examples":[{"text":"دَاء الْكَلَب","english":"rabies, hydrophobia"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"burning thirst"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"greed"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rabid, affected with rabies"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"mad"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"greedy"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *kalb-. Cognate with Akkadian 𒌨𒂠 (kalbum) and Biblical Hebrew כֶּלֶב (kɛ́lɛḇ).\n\nLikely denominal to كَلَب (kalab, “rabies”) or directly to كَلْب (kalb, “dog”).\n\nLikely derived from كَلْب (kalb, “dog”)."},"ipa":["/kalb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37137","headword_ar":"كَلِبَ","root":"klb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a dog)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was seized with madness, in consequence of eating human flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was seized with madness like that of dogs, in consequence of his having been bitten by a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mad"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dog;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was seized with hydrophobia"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) So also a camel. (S, K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuliba","text_ar":"كُلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaniYa","text_ar":"عَنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e., pass. in form, but neut. in signification,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lost his reason by the kind of madness termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalab","text_ar":"كَلَب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAbN","text_ar":"كَلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was angry"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with him; and thus resembled one afflicted with"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2625},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the disease called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalab","text_ar":"كَلَب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was light-witted; weak and stupid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foolish; ignorant; deficient in intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiha","text_ar":"سَفِهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thus resembled one afflicted with the disease called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalab","text_ar":"كَلَب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He thirsted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) From"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ he was seized with the disease of dogs, and died of thirst: ” for the person afflicted with this disease thirsts, and when he sees water, is frightened at it. (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba EalaY $aYo'K","text_ar":"كَلِبَ عَلَى شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was eager for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desired with avidity, a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b8-  In like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu EalaY AlA^amori","text_ar":"النَّاسُ عَلَى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takaAlaba","text_ar":"تَكَالَبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people were eager for the thing, as though they were dogs."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ate voraciously, without becoming satiated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a person bitten by a mad dog)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cried out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barked"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (so accord. to the TA; but accord. to some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaba","text_ar":"كَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astklb","text_ar":"استكلب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a dog)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had the habit of eating men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaba","text_ar":"كَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K: but in some copies,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; [which is evidently the right reading;]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astklb","text_ar":"استكلب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man in a desert place, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barked, in order that dogs might hear him and bark, and that one might be guided thereby to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to receive"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direct him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makolabapN","text_ar":"مَكْلَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed the office of a pimp."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, IAar, K.) [This office seems to be thus compared with that which a dog performs, in inviting travellers, by his bark, to enjoy his master's hospitality.] ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a tree),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having sufficient watering, had rough leaves, without losing their moisture, so that they caught to the garments of those who passed by, thus annoying them like a dog."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ADk, K. *) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a tree)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became stripped of its leaves, and rugged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scabrous, so that it caught to men's garments, and annoyed the persons passing by, like a dog."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaba AlmazAdapN","text_ar":"كَلَبَ المَزادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He inserted a strap, thong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strip of leather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalob","text_ar":"كَلْب"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two edges of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in sewing them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobu","text_ar":"الكَلْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the action of a woman who sews a skin, when, finding the thong too short, she inserts into the hole a double thong, and puts through it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. e. through the loop thus formed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the end of the deficient thong, and then makes it to come out"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the other side of the skin, by pulling the loop through"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IDrd.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kulobapN","text_ar":"كُلْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabati Als~ayori","text_ar":"كَلَبَتِ السَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a female sewer of skins or the like),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"finding the thong"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which she was sewing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"too short, doubled a thong, through which she put the end of the deficient thong"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to draw it through"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaba Als~ayora","text_ar":"كَلَبَ السَّيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sewed the thong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strip of leather, between two other thongs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strips."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi Alqid~u","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ القِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The strap"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thong of untanned hide pressed painfully upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by his being exposed with it to the sun or air, and its drying. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba Ealayohi Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"كَلِبَ عَلَيْهِ الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortune pressed severely upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliybN","text_ar":"كَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and 6. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(winter, S, K, cold, &c., S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became severe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an enemy)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressed hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon him. (TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a rope)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell between the cheek and wheel of the pulley."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabahu","text_ar":"كَلَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck him with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~aAb","text_ar":"كُلَّاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spur."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n37138","headword_ar":"كلّب","root":"klb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takoliybN","text_ar":"تَكْلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He trained"},{"kind":"text","text":"a dog"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to hunt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he trained"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahod","text_ar":"فَهْد"},{"kind":"text","text":", or a bird of prey,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to take game."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) See the act. part. n."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n37142","headword_ar":"كَلْبٌ","root":"klb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known signification, [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dog:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any wounding animal of prey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, &c.:) but whether birds [of prey] are comprised in this term is a point that requires consideration: (Esh-Shiháb El-Khafájee:) and especially applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barking animal"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dog"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or rather, this is its proper signification; and it admits no other: (MF:) sometimes used as an epithet; as in the ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imoraA^apN kalobapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَاَةٌ كَلْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman like a bitch; a woman who is a bitch"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolubN","text_ar":"اَكْلُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (of mult., TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbN","text_ar":"كِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliybN","text_ar":"كَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a rare [form of] pl., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or rather a quasi-pl. n.,] (S,) and (pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolubN","text_ar":"اَكْلُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAlibu","text_ar":"اَكَالِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and (pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbN","text_ar":"كِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbaAtN","text_ar":"كِلَابَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and (also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbN","text_ar":"كِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAliybu","text_ar":"اَكَالِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbN","text_ar":"كِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as a pl. of pauc.;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapu kilaAbK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةُ كِلَابٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being said for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlAvpN mina AlkilaAbi","text_ar":"ثلاثةٌ مِنَ الكِلَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klAb","text_ar":"كلاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being used in this case for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolubK","text_ar":"اَكْلُبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliybN","text_ar":"كَلِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAlibN","text_ar":"كَالِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pack,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collected number, of dogs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [both are quasi-pl. ns. in my opinion, though the former is called a pl. in the S:] accord. to some, the former, if masc., is a quasipl. n. ; and if fem., a pl.: (MF:) the latter is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAmilN","text_ar":"جَامِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqirN","text_ar":"بَاقِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which are both quasi-pl. ns.]. (L.) The pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobapN","text_ar":"كَلْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the fem.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbN","text_ar":"كِلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabaAtN","text_ar":"كَلَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN biwaAdiY Alkalobi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بِوَادِى الكَلْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is in the valley of the dog:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said of one whom no one cares for, and who has no place of abode or resort, but is like a dog, which one sees ever going forth into the desert. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~a Eanohu kilaAbahu","text_ar":"كَفَّ عَنْهُ كِلَابَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He left reviling him, and injuring"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annoying him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit., restrained from him his dogs]. (A.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkilaAbu ElY Albaqar i","text_ar":"الكِلَابُ على البَقَر ِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) the first word being in the nom. case as an inchoative, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkilaAba","text_ar":"الكِلَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) put in the acc. case as governed by a verb understood, (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkiraAbu","text_ar":"الكِرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkiraAba","text_ar":"الكِرَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Kh, S, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"krb","text_ar":"كرب"},{"kind":"text","text":", K;) of which readings, that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlklAb","text_ar":"الكلاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the one generally adopted; (TA;) or they are two distinct proverbs, each having its proper meaning; (Meyd;) the former signifying, [if we read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkilaAba","text_ar":"الكِلَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Send the dogs against the wild oxen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., leave a man and his art: (S, K:) [but accord. to MF, this is the meaning if we read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"krAb","text_ar":"كراب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but if we read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klAb","text_ar":"كلاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", the signification is, as explained above, “ Send the dogs &c., ” and the proverb is applied on the occasion of instigating one set of people against another set, without caring for what may happen to them:] or it alludes to a man's having little care or solicitude for the state, or case, or affair, of his companion. (A 'Obeyd.) If we read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlklAbu","text_ar":"الكلابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dogs are upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against, the wild oxen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, if we read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkrAbu","text_ar":"الكرابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is “ The turning over of the soil is the work of the oxen: ” if"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkrAba","text_ar":"الكرابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ Leave the turning over of the soil to the oxen. ” (MF, from expositions of the Fs.) ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems also to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fierce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furious, dog."},{"kind":"text","text":"See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqanobaApN","text_ar":"عَقَنْبَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobu Albar~i","text_ar":"كَلْبُ البَرِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dog of the desert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wolf."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iy^ob","text_ar":"ذِيْب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also especially applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b8-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first increase of water in a valley."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of iron at the head of the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2626},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pivot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"axis, of a mill."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of wood by which a wall is propped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supported."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain fish"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the form of a dog."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobu AlbaHori","text_ar":"كَلْبُ البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobu AlbaHoriY~u","text_ar":"الكَلْبُ البَحْرِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are appellations now applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The shark."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thong, cut from an untanned skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mukal~abN","text_ar":"مُكَلَّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bound with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalob","text_ar":"كَلْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., with a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thong, cut from an untanned skin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of a hill of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamap","text_ar":"اَكَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~aAbN","text_ar":"كُلَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The nail that is in the hilt of a sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw^aAbap","text_ar":"ذُوَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cord"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other ligature by which the hilt is occasionally attached to the guard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a nail in the hilt of a sword, with which is another"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nail"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEajuwzu","text_ar":"العَجُوزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) and (so accord. to the K: but accord. to the TA, the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cord"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ligature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"itself,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*w^Abp","text_ar":"ذوابة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a sword."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strap, thong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strip of leather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a red"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomar","text_ar":"اَحْمَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=xar","text_ar":"ا=خَر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strap, &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is put between the two edges of a skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is sewed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobu Alfarasi","text_ar":"كَلْبُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streak, that is in the middle of the horse's back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isotawaY","text_ar":"اـِسْتَوَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY kalobi farasihi","text_ar":"عَلَى كَلْبِ فَرَسِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sat firmly upon the line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streak, in the middle of his horse's back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~aAbN","text_ar":"كَلَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An iron at the edge of a camel's saddle of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hooked, iron, by which the traveller hangs, from the saddle"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rHl","text_ar":"رحل"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his travelling-provisions"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adaAwiY","text_ar":"اَدَاوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fahodN","text_ar":"فَهْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything with which a thing is made firm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is bound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~umaA wuv~iqa bihi $aYo'N","text_ar":"كُلُّمَا وُثِّقَ بِهِ شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in some copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwviqa","text_ar":"اُوثِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(as in others): so called because it holds fast a thing like a dog. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEiyrapN","text_ar":"شَعِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Eyrp","text_ar":"شعيرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the handle of a knife &c.]. (S.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnu Alkalobi","text_ar":"لِسَانُ الكَلْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cynoglossum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dog's tongue"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~u Alkalobi","text_ar":"كَفُّ الكَلْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain spreading herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which grows in the plain low tracts of Nejd; thus called when it has dried, in which case it is likened to the paw of a dog; but while it continues green, it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kft","text_ar":"كفت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u kalobK","text_ar":"اُمُّ كَلْبٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain small thorny tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which grows in rugged ground, and upon the mountains, having yellow leaves, and rough; when it is put in motion, it diffuses a most fetid and foul smell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of its thorns, or because it stinks like a dog when rain falls upon him. (TA.)       -A7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u kalobapa","text_ar":"اُمُّ كَلْبَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) So called because it keeps to a man with much tenacity, like a dog. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytu minohu A@sota Alkalobapi","text_ar":"لَقِيتُ مِنْهُ ا@سْتَ الكَلْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a prov.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotN","text_ar":"اِسْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sth","text_ar":"سته"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobu AlA^akobaru","text_ar":"الكَلْبُ الاَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The constellation of Canis Major:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its principal star, Sirius."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Kazweenee &c.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobu AlA^aSogaru","text_ar":"الكَلْبُ الاَصْغَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alklb Almutaqad~imu","text_ar":"الكلب المُتَقَدِّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The constellation of Canis Minor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its principal star, Procyon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Kazweenee &c.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalobu","text_ar":"الكَلْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobu Alr~aAEiY","text_ar":"كَلْبُ الرَّاعِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain star, over against"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~alowu","text_ar":"الدَّلْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.), ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below; in the path of which is a red star, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aAEiY","text_ar":"الرَّاعِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klb","text_ar":"كلب"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrAEY","text_ar":"الراعى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name given to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a star between the feet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs, of Cepheus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrEY","text_ar":"الرعى"},{"kind":"text","text":", to that which is upon his left foot, or leg; (El-Kazweenee;) [app., from their longitudes, the same two stars to which the above quotation from the TA relates: but the same two names are also given to two other stars.] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"klb AlrEY","text_ar":"كلب الرعى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [likewise] a name given to The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"star which is on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in, the head of Hercules;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHAwY","text_ar":"الحاوى"},{"kind":"text","text":", an evident mistake in my MS. of El-Kazweenee, I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAviY","text_ar":"الجَاثِى"},{"kind":"text","text":";] that in the head of Ophiuchus ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaw~aA'u","text_ar":"الحَوَّاءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrAEY","text_ar":"الراعى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (El-Kazweenee.) ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkalobaAni","text_ar":"الكَلْبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Freytag,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A name of the two stars        \n      υ and        \n      κ which belong to Taurus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but accord. to my MS. of El-Kazweenee, the two stars that are near together on the ears of Taurus are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkuloyataAni","text_ar":"الكُلْيَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbu Al$~itaA'i","text_ar":"كِلَابُ الشِّتَاءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterisms, of the beginning of winter; namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iraAEu","text_ar":"الذِّرَاعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alm~avorapu","text_ar":"المَّثْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~arofu","text_ar":"الطَّرْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljabohapu","text_ar":"الجَبْهَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the 7th, 8th, 9th, and 10th, of the Mansions of the Moon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because they set aurorally in the winter: the first so set, about the period of the commencement of the era of the Flight, in central Arabia, on the 3rd of January: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAzilu Alqamari","text_ar":"مَنَازِلُ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzl","text_ar":"نزل"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","MF","Msb","Sb","TA","L"]},{"entry_id":"n37143","headword_ar":"كَلَبٌ","root":"klb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kulaAbN","text_ar":"كُلَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Madness which affects a dog in consequence of eating human flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Madness like that of dogs, which affects a man in consequence of his having been bitten by a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mad"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dog:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disorder"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diobolical possession:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disease that befalls a man from the bite of a mad dog, occasioning what resembles madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diabolical possession, so that whomsoever he bites, that person also becomes in like manner affected, abstaining from drinking water until he dies of thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the Arabs concur in the assertion that its cure is a drop of the blood of a king, mixed with water, and given to the patient to drink. (TA.) Accord. to El-Mufaddal, it originates from a disease which befalls the standing corn &c., and which is not removed until the sun rises upon it: if cattle eat of it before that, they die: wherefore Mohammad forbade pasturing by night: but sometimes a camel runs away, and eats of such pasture before sunrise, and dies in consequence: then a dog comes, and eats of its flesh, and becomes mad; and if it bite a man, he also becomes mad, and when he hears the barking of a dog, answers it [by barking]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaA'u Almuluwki A^a$ofaY mina","text_ar":"دِمَاءُ المُلُوكِ اَشْفَى مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkalabi","text_ar":"الكَلَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The blood of kings has cured of canine madness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, accord. to another reading,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dimaA'u","text_ar":"دِمَاءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuluwki $ifaA'u Alkalabi","text_ar":"المُلُوكِ شِفَاءُ الكَلَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The blood of kings is the cure for canine madness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. A proverb, explained by what is quoted from Lh, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". But some reject this explanation, and assert the meaning to be, that, when a man is enraged [by desire of obtaining revenge], and takes his blood revenge, the blood is the cure of his rage, though not really drunk. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  [Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A madness like that of the dog, affecting camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See 4.)] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kulobapN","text_ar":"كُلْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vehemence; severity; pressure; affliction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intenseness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of cold &c.; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"julobapu","text_ar":"جُلْبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severity and sharpness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of winter: (K, for the former word; and TA, for the latter) also the latter, accord. to the TA, [and the former also, as appears from its verb,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of him or fortune, and of everything: (TA:) and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straitness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) of life: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drought:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress arising from drought"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from government &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEotu Eanoka kalaba fulaAnK","text_ar":"دَفَعْتُ عَنْكَ كَلَبَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have averted from thee the evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief, and injurious conduct, of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","Lth","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n37144","headword_ar":"كَلِبٌ","root":"klb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A dog or man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected with the disease called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) ―         -b2-  A dog"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accustomed to eating human flesh, and in consequence seized with what resembles madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diabolical possession, so that when it wounds a man, he also becomes in like manner affected"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth. S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the disease called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kulaAbN","text_ar":"كُلَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barking like a dog, reading his clothes upon himself. wounding others, and at last dying of thirst, refusing to drink."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth.) ―         -b3-  A man thus affected is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliybN","text_ar":"كَلِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibuwna","text_ar":"كَلِبُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of the latter (or of the former accord. to the S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobaY","text_ar":"كَلْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) When a man thus affected bites another, they come to a man of noble rank, and he drops for them some blood from his finger, which they give to drink to the patient, and he becomes cured. (Lh.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalabN","text_ar":"كَلَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaliba","text_ar":"كَلِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A dog"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"habituated to eating men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  An"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"importunate"},{"kind":"text","text":"beggar. (A.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN kalibN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortune that presses severely and injuriously upon its subjects."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A tree"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the leaves are rough, in consequence of its not having sufficient watering, without losing their moisture, so that they catch to the garments of those who pass by, thus annoying them like a dog."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ADk.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}